    <section class="intro">
        <h2>Understanding the Mines Crisis</h2>
        <p id="info">Cambodia faces significant risks due to landmines and explosive remnants of war from past conflicts. Over 64,843 people have been killed or injured from 1979 to 2019. It is crucial to understand these risks and take appropriate safety measures to protect yourself and your community.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="safety">
        <h2>Stay Safe: Recognize Danger Areas</h2>
        <ul>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> <strong>Warning Signs:</strong> Look out for warning signs and barriers indicating mined areas.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-ban"></i> <strong>Suspicious Objects:</strong> Avoid touching or moving unfamiliar objects in public terrain.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="informed">
        <h2>Stay Informed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-bullhorn"></i> <strong>Local Updates:</strong> Stay updated. Regularly check and familiarise yourself with mine map on community board.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-book"></i> <strong>Spread the Word:</strong> Attend community meetings and inform family, friends and neighbours on mine discovery updates.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="actions">
        <h2>Steps to Take if You Suspect Mines</h2>
        <ul>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-hand-paper"></i> <strong>Do Not Approach:</strong> If you suspect an area is mined, do not approach or enter it.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> <strong>Mark the Area:</strong> If possible, mark the area with a visible sign or object to warn others.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-phone-alt"></i> <strong>Inform Authorities:</strong> Immediately report the suspected area to local authorities, such as community head.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="emergency">
        <h2>What to Do in an Emergency</h2>
        <ul>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> <strong>Remain Calm:</strong> If an explosion occurs or a mine is found, remain calm.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> <strong>Move Away Safely:</strong> Carefully and slowly retrace your steps back to safety.</li>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-ambulance"></i> <strong>Seek Help:</strong> Reach out to locals for assistance by any means, warn them and report to authorities.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="contacts">
        <h2>Key Contacts</h2>
        <p id="info"><i class="fas fa-phone"></i> <strong>Local Authorities:</strong> Keep in regular contact with local authorities by attending community meetings and .</p>
    </section>

    <section class="support">
        <h2>Support and Rehabilitation</h2>
        <ul>
            <li id="info"><i class="fas fa-hospital"></i> <strong>Medical Assistance:</strong> Seek immediate medical help for any injuries.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="importance">
        <h2>Why This Matters</h2>
        <p id="info">Living in areas with unregistered mines poses significant risks. Understanding the dangers and following safety measures can save lives and prevent injuries. Stay informed, stay safe, and always report suspicious areas to authorities.</p>
